u-Kama
Oracle Justification and Metric Design Rationale
Version 1.0 – Governance & Architecture Memorandum
1. Purpose of This Document
This document justifies:
1. Which oracle classes are currently recognised within u-Kama.
2. Why each oracle is necessary and sufficient.
3. Why core system metrics are defined as they are.
4. How these metrics align with ecological constraint rather than financial
optimisation.
5. How each metric maps to Protection (PoP), Base Granular Units (BGUs),
and BDR state transitions.
u-Kama does not optimise for data abundance. It optimises for truth under
constraint.
PART I — ORACLE ARCHITECTURE
u-Kama recognises no sovereign oracle.
Truth may only be recognised through structured exposure across
independent classes of witness.
This follows the Trias Testium Principle:
One witness remembers.
One witness interprets.
One witness contests coherence.
None are permitted sovereignty.
AI is never a witness. It performs coherence checking only.
1. Oracle Classes Currently Used
1. Observational Oracles
Remote, non-human, non-interested instruments.
Examples
Satellite rainfall datasets
Satellite vegetation indices (NDVI type proxies)
Surface water detection
Fixed camera feeds
Seasonal meteorological regime classification
Primary Functions
Declare Seasonal Boolean Gate state.
Detect hydrological persistence.
Confirm spatial integrity of declared ecological cells.
Detect disturbance signals.
Why Required
Ecological state cannot be derived from human testimony alone.
Observational data provides non-intentional recording.
Limitation
Cannot interpret meaning. Only detect state shifts.
2. Laboratory Oracles
Biophysical assays conducted under declared methodology.
Examples
Soil carbon and aggregate stability
Soil microbiology indices
eDNA biodiversity presence confirmation
Water nutrient and sediment testing
Primary Functions
Confirm biological function beyond surface greenness.
Corroborate regenerative directionality.
Detect hidden degradation masked by surface vegetation.
Why Required
Surface indicators alone are insufficient. Regeneration requires biological
function, not merely biomass.
Limitation
Point-in-time sampling. Cannot observe persistence alone.
3. Human Oracles
Named individuals with role accountability.
Examples
Stewards
Rangers
Custodial authority
Community-declared witnesses
Primary Functions
Record subsistence legitimacy.
Detect illegal extraction.
Confirm declared dependency layers.
Trigger Exposure Protocol when contradictions arise.
Why Required
Ecology includes human action. Human pressure cannot be inferred solely
from satellites.
Limitation
Susceptible to bias. Therefore non-sovereign.
4. Dependency Declaration Oracle
A governance oracle.
Function
Declares external dependencies per ecological cell:
Critical
Important
Observational
Why Required
Some features are externally coupled, for example:
Upstream dams
